        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3165061344" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11308267150499496769">This was an impulse listen because I wanted a short audiobook and I knew Agatha Christie is pretty good for easy listening. These were a mixture of short stories, most of which featured people I have not encountered before, though I knew Christie wrote about them. Parker Pyne and Harley Quin are people I haven&apos;t read about before, though I definitely preferred Parker Pyne&apos;s rather interesting manipulation of the setting, rather than Mr Quin&apos;s mildly supernatural way of doing things. <br/><br/>The romance </span>
  <span id="freeText11308267150499496769" style="display:none">This was an impulse listen because I wanted a short audiobook and I knew Agatha Christie is pretty good for easy listening. These were a mixture of short stories, most of which featured people I have not encountered before, though I knew Christie wrote about them. Parker Pyne and Harley Quin are people I haven't read about before, though I definitely preferred Parker Pyne's rather interesting manipulation of the setting, rather than Mr Quin's mildly supernatural way of doing things. <br /><br />The romance short stories in this audiobook are not exactly happy in that respect but they did get me enthralled right up until the very end. It was an eclectic mix of stories and I really enjoyed what we got. It has definitely made me more interested in checking out Christie's other books now that I am almost done with Miss Marple and Poirot stories. 4 stars! </span>
  <a data-text-id="11308267150499496769" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
