        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2351183284" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15377986260351373990"><b>AN UGLY TRUTH</b><br/><br/>Remember when I wrote I had read everything Agatha Christie had written? Well, not being able to face this ugly truth, I scoured the web in order to find some short stories I had overlooked... And, luckily, I found them! They were in English and included in collections (the other one is &quot;<i>The witness for the prosecution and other stories</i>&quot;) the major part of which I had already read, so I selected just the stories I didn&apos;t know. <br/><br/>★★★★✰: &quot;<i>The Harlequin tea set</i>&quot;, &quot;<i>The love detectives</i>&quot; (&quot;</span>
  <span id="freeText15377986260351373990" style="display:none"><b>AN UGLY TRUTH</b><br /><br />Remember when I wrote I had read everything Agatha Christie had written? Well, not being able to face this ugly truth, I scoured the web in order to find some short stories I had overlooked... And, luckily, I found them! They were in English and included in collections (the other one is "<i>The witness for the prosecution and other stories</i>") the major part of which I had already read, so I selected just the stories I didn't know. <br /><br />★★★★✰: "<i>The Harlequin tea set</i>", "<i>The love detectives</i>" ("<i>Gli investigatori dell'amore</i>"), "<i>Magnolia blossom</i>"<br />★★★✰✰: "<i>Problem at Pollensa Bay</i>" ("<i>Il caso della baia di Pollensa</i>"), "<i>The second gong</i>", "<i>Yellow iris</i>" ("<i>Iris gialli</i>"), "<i>The Regatta mystery</i>" ("<i>La stella del mattino</i>"), "<i>Next to a dog</i>"<br /><br />Now I REALLY have finished (sigh!). Goodbye, Agatha, it has been a pleasure!<br /><br />"<i>«You are going?»<br />«To freedom. There is nothing to bind me here.»</i>"</span>
